GREAT LAKES DREDGE & DOCK COMPANY, Appellee, v. THE Steamtug LEHIGH, Interports Transportation Corp’n, Appellee. THE Steam Tug BARWICK, Barwick, Inc., Appellant. No. 424. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 8, 1936. Lynch, Hagen & Atkins, of New York City (Henry C. Eidenbach, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Chauncey I. Clark and Adrian J. O’Kane, both of New York City, for appellee.

Before L. HAND, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree 15 F.Supp. 425 affirmed.
